detaileddescription.para: Snapshot a delta lake table to be an iceberg table. The action will read the delta lake table's log through the table's path, create a new iceberg table using the given icebergCatalog and newTableIdentifier, and commit all changes in one iceberg transaction.
The new table will only be created if the snapshot is successful.

memberdef.argsstring: (long latestVersion, Transaction transaction, ImmutableSet.Builder< String > migratedDataFilesBuilder)
memberdef.name: commitInitialDeltaSnapshotToIcebergTransaction

detaileddescription.para: Commit the initial delta snapshot to iceberg transaction. It tries the snapshot starting from deltaStartVersion tolatestVersion and commit the first constructable one.
There are two cases that the delta snapshot is not constructable:

listitem.para: the version is earlier than the earliest checkpoint
the corresponding data files are deleted byVACUUM

detaileddescription.para: For more information, please refer to delta lake's Data Retention

parameterdescription.para: the latest version of the delta lake table

simplesect.para: the initial version of the delta lake table that is successfully committed to iceberg

memberdef.argsstring: (VersionLog versionLog, Transaction transaction, ImmutableSet.Builder< String > migratedDataFilesBuilder)
memberdef.name: commitDeltaVersionLogToIcebergTransaction

detaileddescription.para: Iterate through theVersionLog to determine the update type and commit the update to the givenTransaction .
1. AppendFiles - when there are only AddFile instances (an INSERT on the table)
2. DeleteFiles - when there are only RemoveFile instances (a DELETE where all the records of file(s) were removed)
3. OverwriteFiles - when there are a mix of AddFile and RemoveFile (a DELETE/UPDATE)

parameterdescription.para: the delta log version to commit to iceberg table transaction
the iceberg table transaction to commit to
